-- Reliance Power to Invest $2 Billion to Set Up Solar Plants, Times Reports
-- B y   V a n d a n a   G o m b a r
-- 2010-09-27T05:36:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/reliance-power-to-invest-2-billion-to-set-up-solar-plants-times-reports.html
Reliance Power Ltd., owned by
Indian billionaire Anil Ambani, plans to spend  about 90 billion
rupees ($2 billion) to set up 600 megawatts of solar capacity in
the states of Rajasthan and Maharashtra, the Times of India
reported today, without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vandana Gombar in New Delhi at 
 vgombar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
